    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-06-04T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-06-04T20:00:00-05:00" n="218"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d218">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/6–548: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Pilcher</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-06-05T10:00:00+09:00"
                            >June 5, 1948—10 a. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 5—12:21 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1260. Large anti-American student parade to be attempted today. Mayor<note n="91"
                        xml:id="d218fn91">K. C. Wu.</note> informs me he has ordered universities
                    participating to be <pb facs="0286" n="276" xml:id="pg_276"/> surrounded by
                    cordons of police to prevent departure of students from campus and that
                    plain-clothes men are being detailed to Consulate offices and other centers of
                    American activities. Report received that students are preparing present
                    anti-American Japan aid petition to Consul General this afternoon. Consulate
                    General being officially closed, Mayor suggests that I do not appear.</p>
                <p>Sent Department, Nanking 1013.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Pilcher</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
